description: The arrest of several fishermen in April exposed a trafficking operation that specialized investigators often describe as 'underestimated.' The scheme involves sending small trawlers out to sea to retrieve drugs dropped in the wake of cargo ships.

description: The US administration is stopping construction on a nearly completed offshore wind farm, operated by the Danish group Orsted, off the northeast coast of the United States.

headline: Libyan coast guards fire on Ocean Viking in international waters
description: The humanitarian vessel operated by the NGO SOS Méditerranée came under automatic gunfire from two masked Libyan coast guards for about 20 minutes on Sunday, August 24.

headline: SpaceX's Starship completes successful test flight after a year of mishaps
description: Elon Musk's company completed the first-ever deployment of a test payload – eight dummy satellites – into space. It was the 10th test for the world's biggest and most powerful rocket, which SpaceX and NASA hope to use to get astronauts back on the moon.

headline: French GPs can now prescribe anti-obesity drugs, but not everyone is convinced
description: France's medicine safety agency has decided to broaden access to Wegovy and Mounjaro, which are not reimbursed by the French national health insurance, and to lower the obesity threshold required for a prescription. Some medical professionals are concerned that the new rules could lead to misuse.

description: Taras Fedorenko, a 25-year-old Ukrainian photographer and videographer based in Kyiv, shares with Le Monde the story of a generation striving for a 'normal' life amid the ongoing conflict with Russia.

headline: Life in the West Bank settlement of Kedem Arava: 'We're not taking anyone's place, there is only sand around us'
description: Established in 2017 near the Jordanian border, the Kedem Arava settlement contains prefabricated homes housing some 60 families, former city dwellers seeking a life closer to nature. While most residents deny ideological motivation, their presence fully aligns with the annexation of Palestinian territory sought by the Israeli far right.

headline: François Truffaut's obsession with Isabelle Adjani
description: 'Adjani, The Famous Stranger' (2/6). While making a name for herself at the Comédie Française, the young actress became the French filmmaker's obsession, who courted her insistently on the set of 'The Story of Adèle H.' in 1975. She resisted him and made her mark with a performance full of restrained violence.
